x4freetext: La data
Activation time - 172, 181, 212, 196 min.
For neutron spectrum determination
Two Clover-type High Purity Ge detectors, each
of four independent n-type Ge crystal in common
cryostat.
1.Movable Li-6 glass detector for neutron
angular distribution from 0 to 80 in steps 10 deg.
2. Li-6/ZnS detector as stationary neutron monitor,
detector positioned 300 mm from target  at angle
40 deg.
3.Stationary Li-6 glass detector mounted at angle
120 deg.,at distance 222 mm for measuring g-ray
background.
.Barium carbonate Ba-C-O3 powder as pressed pellets of
20 mm diameter,1.5 mm thickness, enclosed in
0.1-mm-thick aluminum  cans. Ba-138 enrichment  is
98.04%. Pellets were sandwiched between two 0.06 mm
thick gold foils of typically 160 mg mass.
Placed 4.7 mm in front of neutron production target.
Ba sample mass - 1520.1 mg for Ba-1 sample,
and - 1474.4 mg for Ba-2 sample
.Corrections were made for decay of activated nuclei
flux during irradiation, including variations in
neutron flux. For self-absorption
